    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="820" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Count d’Avila</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Harvey</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State for Foreign Affairs</hi>, <lb/>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-16">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 16, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>I have the honor of handing you, for your information, the enclosed copy of a
                        despatch which the secretary of the Chamber of Deputies, now dissolved,
                        addressed to me under date of the 13th instant, and likewise of the motion
                        which <pb facs="0580" n="508" xml:id="pg_508"/> accompanied the same, made
                        by one of its members, and unanimously voted, on the occasion of
                        communicating to the said Chamber the note which you addressed to the house
                        on the 10th instant.</p>
                <p>I avail of this opportunity to renew the assurances of my most distinguished
                        consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>COUNT D’AVILA.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
